subject: p19028690
History: Cirrhosis and ascites with abdominal distention, to assess for pneumonia.
Findings: In comparison with the study of, there is little interval change and no evidence of acute cardiopulmonary disease. No vascular congestion, pleural effusion, or acute focal pneumonia. Of incidental note is an azygous fissure, of no clinical significance.
